ZIGGZAPPA saved ground while trailing, picked up stride and moved up inside of rivals turning of home, shifted outwardly through upper stretch, but leveled off without reaching contention. SOULFUL TARA was briefly fractious in the starting gate, bumped with an outer rival upon leaving it, set the pace along the inside, sparred with a pair of outer bidders passing the three furlong pole, but yielded to them nearing the lane. INSIGHTFUL MISS received simultaneous contact from rivals on both sides at the start, tugged under snug restraint while stalking inside of rivals and just off the inner rail approaching the turn, but took an awkward step approaching the five sixteenths pole causing the rider to take firm hold and steady, then failed to recover while shifting ground outwardly. I GOTTA BOLT pursued from off of the pace four wide and outside of the main group, then gave way around the turn.
